{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011aBiaXXKqwWC55vM2wXqEW","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully retrieved all three files. Here's a summary of the content:\n\n## File Contents Summary\n\n### 1. Settlement Worker (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`)\n\n**Polling Pattern Overview:**\n- Uses `setTimeout` loop for polling (lines 173-186, `loop()` function)\n- `isRunning` boolean flag controls loop state (line 48)\n- `start()` method initiates the polling loop (lines 189-207)\n- `stop()` method cancels pending timeout and sets flag to false (lines 208-217)\n- `poll()` method exposed for testing (line 221)\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Tracks discovered PDAs and ready PDAs in Sets to avoid redundant processing (lines 44-47)\n- Handles decode errors gracefully by tracking undecodeable PDAs (line 47)\n- Polls for Coinflip and Lord of RNGs accounts by filtering on-chain data (lines 122-158)\n- Calls `onSettleReady()` callback when a round's target slot is reached (line 105)\n- Uses `isFinalized()` callback to clean up tracking sets (line 85)\n- Logs timing metrics for all poll cycles (lines 161-170)\n- Transient RPC errors are caught and logged without crashing (lines 177-182)\n\n### 2. Logger (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/logger.ts`)\n\n**Logger API:**\n- Four log levels: `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error`\n- All methods: `logger.debug(message, fields?)`, `logger.info(message, fields?)`, `logger.warn(message, fields?)`, `logger.error(message, fields?)`\n- Structured JSON output with timestamp, level, message, and context fields\n- Errors go to `process.stderr`, everything else to `process.stdout` (lines 23-27)\n\n### 3. Index Entry Point (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`)\n\n**Worker Startup Pattern:**\n- Settlement worker is created and started on app initialization (lines 148-159)\n- Dependencies injected: `db`, `connection`, `serverKey`, `pollIntervalMs`, callbacks\n- `onSettleReady` callback triggers settlement attempt via `retrySettler` (line 154)\n- `isFinalized` callback integrated to check if PDA is already settled (line 157)\n- Close Call clock worker also started (lines 163-168)\n- Worker status exposed via `isWorkerRunning()` getter for health endpoints (line 202)\n\nAll files are complete and ready for reference."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a257c4f0aaced86f6 (use SendMessage with to: 'a257c4f0aaced86f6' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40467\ntool_uses: 8\nduration_ms: 54981</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"787712eb-bdb6-4c19-96b6-c592da678f59","uuid":"efe91b50-66e7-41ee-836b-49d00e36c354","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:17:22.684Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read the settlement worker in `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/` to understand the polling pattern (setTimeout loop, isRunning flag, start/stop, shutdown). Also read `src/logger.ts` for the logger API. Also read `src/index.ts` to see how workers are started. Return the full content of these files.","agentId":"a257c4f0aaced86f6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully retrieved all three files. Here's a summary of the content:\n\n## File Contents Summary\n\n### 1. Settlement Worker (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/settlement.ts`)\n\n**Polling Pattern Overview:**\n- Uses `setTimeout` loop for polling (lines 173-186, `loop()` function)\n- `isRunning` boolean flag controls loop state (line 48)\n- `start()` method initiates the polling loop (lines 189-207)\n- `stop()` method cancels pending timeout and sets flag to false (lines 208-217)\n- `poll()` method exposed for testing (line 221)\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Tracks discovered PDAs and ready PDAs in Sets to avoid redundant processing (lines 44-47)\n- Handles decode errors gracefully by tracking undecodeable PDAs (line 47)\n- Polls for Coinflip and Lord of RNGs accounts by filtering on-chain data (lines 122-158)\n- Calls `onSettleReady()` callback when a round's target slot is reached (line 105)\n- Uses `isFinalized()` callback to clean up tracking sets (line 85)\n- Logs timing metrics for all poll cycles (lines 161-170)\n- Transient RPC errors are caught and logged without crashing (lines 177-182)\n\n### 2. Logger (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/logger.ts`)\n\n**Logger API:**\n- Four log levels: `debug`, `info`, `warn`, `error`\n- All methods: `logger.debug(message, fields?)`, `logger.info(message, fields?)`, `logger.warn(message, fields?)`, `logger.error(message, fields?)`\n- Structured JSON output with timestamp, level, message, and context fields\n- Errors go to `process.stderr`, everything else to `process.stdout` (lines 23-27)\n\n### 3. Index Entry Point (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/index.ts`)\n\n**Worker Startup Pattern:**\n- Settlement worker is created and started on app initialization (lines 148-159)\n- Dependencies injected: `db`, `connection`, `serverKey`, `pollIntervalMs`, callbacks\n- `onSettleReady` callback triggers settlement attempt via `retrySettler` (line 154)\n- `isFinalized` callback integrated to check if PDA is already settled (line 157)\n- Close Call clock worker also started (lines 163-168)\n- Worker status exposed via `isWorkerRunning()` getter for health endpoints (line 202)\n\nAll files are complete and ready for reference."}],"totalDurationMs":54981,"totalTokens":40467,"totalToolUseCount":8,"usage":{"input_tokens":2780,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5861,"cache_read_input_tokens":31166,"output_tokens":660,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5861},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
